Commit Message: Initial commit
Parsing dates
Changed a print-statement to be more Python 3 friendly, as suggested by @peremen
Requirements
38-series
Fix deprectation warning

Argparse, and xelatex option

Now using argparse, which has the option `--xelatex` that adds `\-` in the URL.
Fix: Changes in requirements after security alert on request

Documentation: Add issue tracker badge in README

Adding a shield (shields.io) for the number of open issues in Github
to the README.md text.

Documentation: Add License badge

Added LICENSE in #4, so now we're adding a badge for it. Because who doesn't
like more badges?

Create License

Choosing MIT license to be permissive.

Create .gitigore

The .gitignore file is based on
https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/master/Python.gitignore

Create Makefile

This Makefile contains a test target so that one can run `make test`. There
is a `init` target as well for installing dependencies.

Refactor: Move output files to output directory

The generated example .bib-files are moved to the `output` directory to keep
the directory clean.

Create setup.py

A stub setup.py is created in the root directory.

Refactor: Move Python files to module

Moved `3gpp-citations.py` to `3gpp-citations` module directory and created
empty `__init__.py`.

Add `data` to .gitignore

The `data` directory contains input data, such as Excel exports from the
3GPP-portal. We want to hide it from `git status`.

Fix: Backport open to Python 2 in setup.py

In setup.py, we open the `README.md` file for use as a long description,
and we used a Python 3-way of opening the file. Importing `open` from `io`
solves this problem.

Refactor: Rename submodule

Renaming submodule 3gpp-citations (not valid name) to standardcitations. To be
able to use this as before (in order to have no changes in functionality) we add
the `3gpp-citations` script.

This affects `setup.py` slightly.

Create MANIFEST.in

MANIFEST.in tells Distutils what files to include in the source distribution,
i.e. this file decides what gets included when running for example
`python setup.py install sdist`.

Enhancement: Add generated bib-files as examples

This is a change in `setup.py` where we add the files to
`setup(data_files=...)`. They will be installed with the package.

Refactor: Rename output to examples

The directory containing .bib-files is renamed to examples, and all
references to it are changed as well.

Enhancement: Author information in setup.py

Added my name and email in `setup()`.

Enhancement: Prepare package for testing with py.test

Include dependencies for py.test in requirements.txt and setup.py. Modification
in Makefile to run tests.

Fix: Upgrade pyyaml to 4.2b4

This is a security fix regarding
[CVE-2017-18342](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2017-18342). Fixed
by upgrading Â´pyyaml` to 4.2b4.

Enhancement: Using Travis CI and Coveralls

Create .travis.yml that runs testcases and uploads code coverage to Coveralls.
At the same time, display a code coverage badge on the README.

Enhancement: Add placeholder test

This is adding a test placeholder that only contains `pass`. This will
allow py.test to exit with exitcode 0, which in turn will make Travis complete
the that part of the build without issues.

Fix: Long line in EPILOG

The EPILOG constant contains an example bibtex entry that had a very long
line. Adding line-break takes care of the PEP-8 issue that was found with
py.test.

Enhancement: Travis build badge on README

Now proudly displaying build status on the README with a badge.

Documentation: Add WASP acknowledgment to README

Add a small statement to the README that this work was supported by WASP.

Documentation: Add Contribution guide

Adding contribution guide as CONTRIBUTING.md with link from README.md. Adding
also a link to Gitter IM which we intend to use as a community forum.

Test: Adding test-cases for the parse_args function.

The parse_args function is responsible for setting the input and output
filenames as an option. There is also a flag for XeLaTeX. This commit
adds three test cases.
Documentation: Replace Refactoring tag with Refactor

Fix: Removed check if module is running as main program

The check `if __name__ == '__main__'` is unnecessary when using a script
as an entry point and only reduces code coverage. Hence we remove the check.

Test: Add a test case with flipped input and output fields

Make sure that the input and output files are read correctly
even when they are entered in another order

Test: Align Makefile with Travis CI

Align the command `make test` with the command run in Travis.

Test: Drop py.test in before_script.

Py.test was running the coverage report twice, dropped the one in the
before-script.

Test: Remove placeholder test

The placeholder test was used to get around an exit-code 5 issue when there
were not test cases. Now we have test-cases so this can be removed.

Refactor: Extract method for parsing row

Extract method `parse_row` for parsing a row in the Excel sheet.

Refactor: Rename variable

Renamed `type` (reserved word) to `doctype`.

Refactor: Extract method for formatting entry

The function `format_entry(number, title, doctype, url)` was extracted. This
function returns the formatted bibtex-entry as a dict.

Test: Create test cases for format_entry

We add test cases to verify the that entry
 - type is `dict`
 - ENTRYTYPE is `techreport`
 - contains the expected information (from input)

Documentation: Add Test tag to CONTRIBUTING.md

We are using the Test tag to tag any commit that improves on test cases.
We now add this to the documentation.

Refactor: Extract method for formatting url

The url field is slightly different if the xelatex is used. In such
case it inclides "\-".

Test: New tests for `format_url`.

Adding tests for formatting of the url with or without xelatex, where we use
`\-` to indicate hyphenation.

Documentation: Added introduction

The purpose was missing. Fixed!

Refactor: Extract method parse_date

We extract the method parse_date and rewrite it to actually parse the date.

Test: Add test case for date_format

The test is designed to test that the parsed date is correct, and that the
output is string.

Fix: Removed sys module

sys was unused, removed.

Refactor: Extract method get_bibdatabase

Extracted method for creating an empty BibDatabase

Test: Add test for get_bibdatabase

Test that we can create an empty database of the correct type.

Refactor: Extract method get_workbook

We extract a method for opening the first sheet of a workbook.

Test: Add test for get_workbook

We add a test case for opening a workbook and returning the first sheet. We use
an input file that is derived from an exported file from the 3gpp portal.

Test: Add testcase for the parse_row function

Test the parse row function by reading the `test_input.xlsx` workbook
and reading the first (real) row.

Refactor: Rename variable `row` => `release_row`

The name row was re-used from earlier, which made the code hard to read.

Refactor: Extract method get_entry

Extract method for parsing an entire row and generating an entry.

Test: Add test case for get_entry

The get_entry method is tested by reading the test data and reading
the first real row. The test checks that the entry contains some
expected information.

Test: Add test case for reading empty row

If the row in the Excel sheet is empty the get_entry function
should return None

Refactor: Pull up/move method for creating workbook

Since we call the `get_workbook` in each test case we lift this up to the
`setup_module` function.

Refactor: Extract method `write_bibtex`

Extract the method for writing the database to a file.

Test: Add test cases for `write_bibtex`

We test that the output on stdput or to file matches the expected when
reading from the `test_input.xlsx` file.

Refactor: Inline Temp

Inlining number of rows (ws.max_row - 1).

Test: Add test for main function

This test tests the entire pipeline in context. The tests check that
the output file starts with the correct word and that there are three
items in the file. Complete correctness is tested elsewhere.

Enhancement: Improve Makefile by adding clean targets.

Add two targets, clean-build and clean-pyc. The first removes `build`,
`dist` and `.egg`-files, and the second removes all `.pyc` and. `.pyo`.

Enhancement: Add build target to Makefile

Run `python setup.py sdist bdist_wheel` with `make build`

Fix: Changes in setup.py before PyPI deployment.

In order to deploy our package we fix a few things in setup.py
such as the install requirements.

We also switch to setuptools if it is installed.

Enhancement: Automatic PyPI deployment of tags.

Adding automatic deployment of tags in Travis.
Release: Change version to v1.0.0

Documentation: Add installation instructions

Since our package is on PyPI, we can add installation instructions.
Documentation: Add PyPI version badge
Documentation: Python 2.7.10 message in README

Refactor: Rename method parse_row to parse_excel_row

This function parses an Excel row, so we'll rename it to parse_excel_row
to better reflect what it does.

Renaming is done in standardcitation.py and in test_parse_excel_row.py
(which itself is renamed by this commit)
Documentation: Fix typos in the description.

Test: Add validation of url to test_format_url.

Add a test of the validity of the url. We are using the package `validators`,
which means we are updating requirements and setup as well.
Test: Improve readability of test_parse_excel_row
Test: Improve readability of test_parse_args
Test: Improve readability of test_write_bibtex

Test: Improve test_get_entry by validating date fields

Adding a check on year, month and day fields by allowing them to be within
a range. Implicitly checks if they are integers by converting to int first.
Test: Improve readability of test_format_entry

Test: Test required and relevant fields exist in test_format_entry

This adds a few lines checking that required fields for @techreport exist.

Test: Add test_get_entry_required_fields test

This test makes sure we didn't remove required fields from the get_entry_format
function.
Test: Improve readability of test_get_entry
Update issue templates
Create CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md

Documentation: Add link to CODE_OF_CONDUCT in README.md

Since we created a CODE_OF_CONDUCT, we should link to it in the documentation.

Fix: Lint missing-docstring

Add docstring to standardcitations.py and 3gpp-citations:

This project aims to generate BiBTeX (http://www.bibtex.org/) files that
can be used when citing 3GPP (3gpp.org) specifications. The input is a document
list exported from the  3GPP Portal (https://portal.3gpp.org/).

Fix: Lint superfluous-parens

We had a superfluous parenthesis around a print statement which was
solved by `from __future__ import print_function`. We had to reorder
the imports to avoid further wrong-import-order lint errors.

Enhancement: Add pylint module

We add pylint module and a `lint` make target for our convenience.

Fix: lint anomalous-backslash-in-string

We fix a lint warning by 1) adding an r to make the docstring raw and
2) disabling the first pylint warning with a comment.

Fix: Lint literal-comparison

We compared a string to "" which was a no-no.

Fix: Lint superfluous-parens

Removing superfluous parenthesis around if statement.

Fix: Lint bad-continuation

Remove three spaces to make line continuation conform to pylint standards.

Refactor: Rename variable

This fixes a invalid-name lint warning in `get_bibdatabase` for `db` which
was anyways never a good name.

Refactor: Rename variable ws

This fixes a invalid-name lint warning in `get_workbook` for `ws` which
was anyways never a good name for a worksheet

Refactor: Rename variable db

This fixes a invalid-name lint warning in `write_bibtex` for `db` which
was anyways never a good name. Renamed to bib_database.

Refactor: Rename variable db

This fixes a invalid-name lint warning in `main` for `db` which
was anyways never a good name. Renamed to bib_database.

Refactor: Rename variable db

This fixes a invalid-name lint warning in `main` for `wd` which
was anyways never a good name. Renamed to worksheet.

Refactor: Rename method get_workbook to get_worksheet

This function returns a worksheet from a workbook so it makes sense
to name it `get_worksheet`.

Refactor: Clean dependencies

Move all dependencies to `setup()`, and add an extra target so that all
(including test)  dependencies can be installed with `pip install .[test]`.

This change is reflected also in the Travis build configuration which is
updated to Python 3.7.

requirements.txt is therefore no longer needed and removed.

Test: Adding pylint and flakes to the test make target.

Add pylint and flakes to the `make test` target forces us to deal with
issues in the test-functions by making the automatic builds fail.

This is reflected also in .travis.yml so that the same tests are run
both locally and on Travis.

Test: Fix unused argument 'module' (unused-argument) in test_format_entry

Removing the `module` argument in setup_module since it was not used.

Test: Fix unused argument 'module' (unused-argument) in test_get_entry

Removing the `module` argument in setup_module since it was not used.

Test: Fix unidiomatic-typecheck lint warning in test_format_entry

Using type() instead of isinstance() for a typecheck. (unidiomatic-typecheck).
Replace `type()` with `isinstance()`.

Test: Fix lint warning unidiomatic-typecheck in test_get_bibdatabase

Using type() instead of isinstance() for a typecheck. (unidiomatic-typecheck)
Changing type() to isinstance(., BibDatabase).

Test: Fix lint warning wrong-import-order in test_format_url.py

Reorder imports to get rid of warning.
Test: Remove unnecessary print in test_format_url

Test: Fix lint warning anomalous-backslash-in-string

Anomalous backslash in string: '\-'. String constant might be missing an r
prefix. (anomalous-backslash-in-string). So we add prefix in two places.

Test: Fix lint warning invalid-name in test_get_worksheet

Variable name `ws` doesn't conform to snake_case naming style (invalid-name),
so we rename it to `worksheet`.

Test: Fix lint warning invalid-name in test_write_bibtex

Variable name `ws` doesn't conform to snake_case naming style (invalid-name),
so we rename it to `worksheet` in two instances (in test_write_bibtex_file and
test_write_bibtex_stdout).

Test: Add multiple Python version to Travis

This change is for Travis to run tests on Python 2.7, 3.5, 3.6 and 3.7.

Release version 1.1.0

Update setup.py with new version number.

Documentation: Installation instructions

Removing the note about Python 2.7 and adding information on how to install
the test dependencies.

Enhancement: Add Trove classification

Add Trove classification according to PEP-301
(https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0301/#distutils-trove-classification).

Documentation: Add PyPI badges for downloads and version numbers

Trove classification in setup.py should mean we can use the version number
badge from shields.io.

Release version 1.1.1

We have updated Trove classification and documentation. To make sure this
change goes through at PyPI we need to create a release.

Fix: PyPI URL pointed to test-server

Correct url is https://pypi.org/project/3gpp-citations/

Documentation: Add badges

Add badges for Code Climate maintainability and Github repo hit count.

Enhancement: Add clean target to Makefile

Clean target depends on clean-build and clean-pyc

Fix: Update setup.py to best practices level

We update setup() with classifiers, python_requires, etc to comply
with best practices.
Refactor: Remove unused imports from setup.py
Release version 1.1.3

Fix: Adding python-coveralls=2.9.1 to test requirements

After removing requirements.txt, coveralls was not working and sometimes
failing the build. We also needed the dependency coverage=4.5.2.

Fix: Replaced license in setup with single statement.

The issue is that the multiple lines in the `License` field are causing the
rest of the file to be interpreted as the `Long-Description`.

See https://github.com/pypa/twine/issues/454 and
https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/issues/1390
Release version 1.1.4

Enhancement: Build wheel on PyPI deployment.

We add the bdist_wheel target beside the already existing sdist target to the
PyPI deployment stage on Travis.

See https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/deployment/pypi/

Enhancement: Update base image to Bionic

We upgrade the base image used for CI testing on Travis to Bionic.

Documentation: Add link to SW testing presentation in README

We add the link to the presentation made in the WASP course workshop to
the README.

Documentation: Fix issues from Markdown lint

Change small issues found my Markdown lint (mdl).
